      <div class="main-body">
        <h1>Find a chlamydia test</h1>
        <p class="body-copy">This service can help you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>find places to go to for a test</li>
          <li>get a home test kit (you may have to pay for this)</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="green-button" href="URL">Start now</a>
        <p class="body-copy">This service is for people in England only.</p>
        <p class="body-copy">Your answers may be used to help improve the NHS website.
          Read the <a href="URL">NHS.UK privacy policy</a>.</p>
        <h2>Others ways to get help</h2>
        <h3>England:</h3>
        <p class="body-copy">To speak to someone, call the
          sexual health helpline for advice on 0300 123 7123. Open Monday to Friday, 9am to 8pm.</p>
        <h3>Scotland:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>use the <a href="URL">Sexual Health Scotland website</a></li>
          <li>call Sexual Health Scotland on 0800 22 44 88 (open Monday to Friday,
            8am to 10pm; Saturday and Sunday, 9am to 5pm)</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Wales:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>use the <a href="URL">NHS Direct Wales website</a></li>
          <li>call NHS Direct Wales on 0845 46 47 (open 24 hours a day, every day)</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Northern Ireland:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>use the <a href="URL">Sexual Health NI website</a></li>
          <li>call the Family Planning Association sexual health helpline on 0345
            122 8687 (open Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm; closed on bank holidays)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="body-copy"><a href="URL">Find out about call charges on GOV.UK</a></p>
      </div>
